JO  - Diabetes Care
AB  - This randomized controlled trial examined the efficacy of metformin in 200 adults aged 45-65 with newly diagnosed type 2 diabetes. Participants received either metformin 1000mg twice daily or placebo for 12 months. Primary outcome was change in HbA1c levels. Results showed a significant reduction in HbA1c (mean difference -1.2%, p<0.001) in the metformin group compared to placebo. Secondary outcomes included fasting glucose and body weight, both showing favorable trends. Metformin was well-tolerated with minimal gastrointestinal side effects.
