JO  - American Journal of Clinical Nutrition
AB  - This 6-month trial randomized 180 overweight adults (BMI 27-35) to either a low-carbohydrate diet (<50g/day) or a low-fat diet. Primary outcomes included changes in LDL cholesterol, HDL cholesterol, and triglycerides. Both groups lost weight, but the low-carb group showed greater improvements in HDL cholesterol (+8.3 mg/dL vs +2.1 mg/dL) and triglycerides (-43 mg/dL vs -18 mg/dL). Blood pressure reductions were similar between groups. Results indicate low-carb diets may offer cardiovascular benefits beyond weight loss.
